comments: During the screen, Curry (GSW) and Brooks (MEM) mutually engage and disengage, and the contact is marginal.
Toscano-Anderson (GSW) turns the corner and marginal contact occurs as he briefly places a resting arm on Melton's (MEM) side during his post move.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) establishes himself in a screening position in Payton II's (GSW) path and absorbs the contact on the pick.
Toscano-Anderson (GSW) jumps vertically and avoids contact with Jackson Jr.'s (MEM) arm while contesting the driving shot attempt.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) reaches for the ball and marginal contact occurs as he brushes Green's (GSW) back during the rebound.
Brooks (MEM) reaches across Curry (GSW) and makes contact with his legs, which affects his SQBR.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) could be deemed to be in the lane for less than three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Porter Jr. (GSW) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Morant (MEM), and any "high-five" contact after the release is deemed incidental.
Bane (MEM) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Brooks (MEM) maintains a legal guarding position on Curry (GSW) as he loses control of his dribble on the perimeter.
Morant (MEM) is in the paint for less than three seconds when Curry (GSW) loses control of the ball.
Brooks (MEM) legally contests Curry's (GSW) jump shot attempt.
There is no clear and conclusive camera angle to determine if Curry (GSW) steps on the sideline out of bounds during his drive to the basket.
Porter Jr. (GSW) and Melton (MEM) mutually engage and disengage off-ball, and the contact is marginal.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Curry (GSW).
Green (GSW) moves into and makes contact with Jackson Jr.'s (MEM) body, which affects his SQBR at the start of his drive.
Green (GSW) briefly places two hands on Jackson Jr.'s (MEM) side as he dribbles on the perimeter, and the contact is marginal.
Green (GSW) legally contests Morant's (MEM) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Payton II (GSW) jumps alongside of Melton (MEM) and collapses his forearm to absorb the contact during his shot near the rim.
Bane (MEM) commits a take foul on Toscano-Anderson (GSW).
Green (GSW) legally contests and cleanly blocks Bane's (MEM) jump shot attempt.
Bane (MEM) commits a take foul on Curry (GSW).
Kuminga (GSW) legally contests Morant's (MEM) jump shot attempt as the game clock expires.
